<subSubSection pageId="634" pageNumber="635" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="634" pageNumber="635">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="634" pageNumber="635">
This rarely collected species is known from southern Ontario (Lindroth 1969a: 959), northern Ohio (Ashtabula County, Harry J. Lee, Jr. pers. comm. 2008), southern Michigan (Clinton County, CMNH), northern and southwestern Indiana (LeConte 1847: 418; Ball 1959: 205), western Illinois, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Tennessee”">&quot;Tennessee&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Ball 1959: 205), southwestern Alabama (Lindroth 1954b: 153), and Connecticut (New London County, Foster F. Purrington pers. comm. 2009). Most old (pre-1950s) records of this species refer to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lindroth" authorityYear="1954" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Badister" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="634" pageNumber="635" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neopulchellus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="634" pageNumber="635">Badister neopulchellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
